{"id":1316914786,"question_id":2,"lang":"rust","lang_name":"Rust","time":"2 weeks, 1 day","timestamp":1720648864,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"0 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1316914786/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"2.2 MB","code":"\nimpl Solution {\n    pub fn add_two_numbers(\n        l1: Option<Box<ListNode>>,\n        l2: Option<Box<ListNode>>,\n    ) -> Option<Box<ListNode>> {\n        let (mut p1, mut p2) = (l1, l2);\n        let mut dummy_head = ListNode::new(0);\n        let mut current = &mut dummy_head;\n        let mut carry = 0;\n\n        while p1.is_some() || p2.is_some() {\n            let mut sum = carry;\n            if let Some(node) = p1 {\n                sum += node.val;\n                p1 = node.next;\n            }\n            if let Some(node) = p2 {\n                sum += node.val;\n                p2 = node.next;\n            }\n\n            carry = sum / 10;\n            current.next = Some(Box::new(ListNode::new(sum % 10)));\n            current = current.next.as_mut().unwrap();\n        }\n\n        if carry > 0 {\n            current.next = Some(Box::new(ListNode::new(carry)));\n        }\n\n        dummy_head.next\n    }\n}\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
